ref: Conf: 6.All-Union Conf.on Neutron Physics,Kiev,2-6 Oct.1983, Vol.3, p.139 (1983)
title: Measurement of the average SIGMA-TOT and SIGMA-SCT cross-sections and resonance blocking-factors for the niobium, molybdenum and cadmium at neutron energy 24.4 keV.

x4freetext: Measurement of the average SIGMA-TOT and SIGMA-SCT
for the  niobium, molybdenum and cadmium

x4codes.shortRef: Conf: 6.All-Union Conf.on Neutron Physics,Kiev,2-6 Oct.1983, Vol.3, p.139 (1983)

x4freetext: Thermal power reactor of obninsk Atomic
Neutron filter consisting of 163 g/cm2 iron,
24.4 keV, energy spread 0.5 keV, flux 4.E+3 n/cm2/sec.
Battery of ten He-3 counters of the `CHM-18`
(alias SNM-18) type , places as ring  plex
cylinder of 350 mm long, inner diameter 65 mm, outer
diameter 140 mm. Detector was covered by Cd of 1mm
Metal samples of natural Cd, Nb, Mo of 99.9% purity .
Background was measured by Ti filter.
Duplicative line in Subent 016 DATA block was deleted.
